title: Paternity Forms (Family Court Act Article 5)
content:
Paternity Forms (Family Court Act Article 5)

State Regulations

Form 5-1 - Paternity petition

Form 5-1-a - Summons-paternity (service within NYS)

Form 5-1-b - Summons-paternity-non-party spouse or former spouse

Form 5-1c - Summons-paternity-non-resident

Form 5-2 - Paternity petition-person other than parent; representative of society

Form 5-3 - Paternity

Form 5-4 - Notice of motion-challenge to testing directive

Form 5-4a - Order-challenge to testing directive

Form 5-5 - Order-vacate acknowledgment of paternity

Form 5-6 - Order for genetic marker test

Form 5-6a - Paternity-temporary order of support on default

Form 5-7 - Paternity-order of filiation

Form 5-7a - Paternity-order of filiation-non-article 5/5-B petition

Form 5-9 - Remand commitment (undertaking)

Form 5-15 - Paternity-petition to acknowledgment of paternity

Form 5-17a - Paternity-motion to vacate for lack of service

Form 5-17b - Paternity-affidavit in support of motion to vacate for lack of service

Form 5-18 - Paternity-order on motion to vacate for lack of service

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
